    <h3>Air-Cooled vs Water-Cooled Batch Freezers</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Air-cooled</strong>: Uses ambient air to cool the condenser. Easier to install (no water connection needed), but generates heat in the room. Less efficient in hot Indian summers when ambient temperature exceeds 40°C. Suitable for smaller machines up to 10 L/batch.</li>
      <li><strong>Water-cooled</strong>: Uses a water circuit to cool the condenser. More efficient in hot climates, quieter, and doesn't heat up the room. Requires a water connection and may need a cooling tower for larger setups. Recommended for machines above 10 L/batch and for Indian conditions.</li>
    </ul>

