    <h2>4. Gelato Machines: Pasteurizer + Batch Freezer</h2>

    <p>Gelato is denser and more flavourful than regular ice cream — it uses more milk than cream, less sugar, and is churned at a slower speed to incorporate less air (25–30% overrun vs 50–100% for ice cream). Making authentic gelato requires specific equipment.</p>

    <h3>Gelato Equipment Overview</h3>
    <p>A complete <strong>gelato machine India</strong> setup typically requires:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Pasteurizer</strong>: Heats the gelato base to 85°C to kill bacteria, then cools it to 4°C for ageing. This is legally required under FSSAI regulations if you're making base from scratch. Price: ₹1,50,000 – ₹4,00,000 depending on capacity (10–60 L).</li>
      <li><strong>Batch Freezer</strong>: Churns and freezes the aged base into gelato. Same as hard ice cream batch freezers described above, but gelato-specific models run at slightly slower speeds for lower overrun.</li>
      <li><strong>Blast Freezer / Shock Freezer</strong>: Rapidly brings the gelato from -7°C (out of the batch freezer) to -18°C for storage. Price: ₹80,000 – ₹3,00,000.</li>
      <li><strong>Gelato Display Vitrine</strong>: The curved-glass display case with temperature-controlled pans where customers choose their flavour. This is the centrepiece of any gelato shop.</li>
    </ol>

