    <h3>Key Margin Drivers</h3>
    <p>Ice cream businesses enjoy <strong>60–70% gross margins</strong> because:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Raw material costs are low: a litre of soft serve mix costs ₹100–₹200 and yields 8–14 servings</li>
      <li>Overrun (air incorporation) effectively stretches your raw material</li>
      <li>Cones and cups cost ₹2–₹5 each</li>
      <li>Toppings and sauces cost ₹1–₹3 per serving</li>
      <li>Perceived value is high — customers willingly pay ₹40–₹200 for a product that costs ₹10–₹50 to make</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Seasonality is the main risk</strong>: In North India, ice cream sales drop 40–60% during winter (November–February). Southern and Western India have more consistent year-round demand. Plan your cash flow accordingly — summer profits must cover winter lean months.</p>

    <p>To offset seasonality, many ice cream parlours also serve hot beverages, waffles, brownies, and other desserts during winter. Having a <a href="/blog/sugarcane-juice-machine-india">sugarcane juice machine</a> in summer adds another high-margin revenue stream.</p>

    <h2>11. Maintenance, Warranty & After-Sales Support</h2>

    <p>Ice cream machines run under demanding conditions — freezing temperatures inside, often 40°C+ outside in Indian summers. Proper maintenance is critical:</p>

    <h3>Daily Maintenance</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Clean all mix-contact parts (hoppers, cylinders, nozzles, gaskets) at the end of each day</li>
      <li>Sanitise with food-grade sanitiser solution</li>
      <li>Check mix levels before opening</li>
      <li>Ensure the condenser is not blocked by dust or debris</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Weekly Maintenance</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Deep clean the entire mix path with hot water and detergent</li>
      <li>Inspect and lubricate O-rings and seals</li>
      <li>Check scraper blades for wear</li>
      <li>Clean the condenser with a brush or compressed air</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Quarterly / Annual Maintenance</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Professional inspection of the refrigeration system</li>
      <li>Refrigerant level check</li>
      <li>Electrical connections inspection</li>
      <li>Replace worn scraper blades and gaskets</li>
      <li>Annual cost for professional servicing: ₹5,000 – ₹15,000 per visit</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Warranty Considerations</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Premium brands (Taylor, Carpigiani)</strong>: 1–2 year comprehensive warranty, extended warranty options available</li>
      <li><strong>Mid-range brands (Oceanpower, Spaceman)</strong>: 1 year parts warranty, 6–12 months labour</li>
      <li><strong>Budget brands (Chinese OEM, local)</strong>: 3–6 months warranty, often limited to compressor only</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Always negotiate the warranty before purchase. A 1-year comprehensive warranty is the minimum you should accept. For machines above ₹2,00,000, insist on an AMC (Annual Maintenance Contract) option.</p>

